What is a Context Menu?

A Context Menu is a menu that appears when a user right-clicks on a record, list column header, field label, or form element in ServiceNow. It provides quick access to commonly used actions and options.

🔹 Features
Accessed using right-click.
Provides shortcuts for frequently used actions.
Available in lists, forms, fields, and column headers.
Changes depending on the selected item and user permissions.
🔹 Common Context Menu Options
For List Records
Open Record
Edit Record
Copy Sys ID
Export Data
Show Matching
Filter Out
For Column Headers
Sort Ascending
Sort Descending
Group By
Configure List Layout
Filter Records
For Form Fields
Personalize Form
Show Dictionary
Configure Dictionary
View Audit History
🔹 Benefits
Faster navigation and record management.
Reduces the number of clicks needed to perform actions.
Improves productivity for administrators and developers.
Provides quick access to configuration options.
🔹 Example Uses

✅ Right-click a Priority column → Sort records by priority.

✅ Right-click a record → Open, edit, or export the record.

✅ Right-click a field label → View dictionary details or configure the field.
